The What's New feature is aimed at people who upgrade their Jira (Confluence, etc) with every release.  However, a lot of us can't do that so we end up jumping several versions when we upgrade. The what's new items are lost.  There is an inverse problem that some what's new items aren't actually relevant to specific sites but we have an all or nothing approach.

I'd like to be able to (1) specify what features are covered in what's new, and (2) to be able to include features from previous releases.  Real nice would be (3) the ability to add your own what's new items to cover site-specific changes, eg, changes to custom workflows.

This library approach could be used as ongoing training too when something needs to be communicated to users asynchronously to version upgrades.  It would also be linked to a menu item to allow users to refresh an update that had checked off previously.

